People must go to WCPU for Demandeurs Visa before their interview in the Section Consulaire; the costly waiting times will be reduced.
From 10 January 2011 the procedure for the treatment of visas at the Embassy and consulates in the United States will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to submit to WCPU for Demandeurs of Visa (CSA, according to its initials) before their interview in Section Consulaire.
The CSA will take biometric information, which will be reviewed by the Section Consulaire before the interview.
The new procedure will present some benefits for candidates, including mentions the following:
The total cost to deal with the visa will be lower, it will no longer be necessary to make a payment for an appointment, another payment for the treatment of the visa and another for the courier service delivers the document.
The aspiring will make a single payment which will cover the three services.
The current tariff will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visas with application (ci-inclut visas for temporary workers) and $390 for the visas of traders and investors.
The people who want to renew their visas will not go to an interview with the Representative Consulaire, they will arise only to the CSA closer to where they will present the documents and take their fingerprints.
Because biometric information will be made in the CSA, applicants who want a second appointment to be interviewed in the Section Consulaire remain less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants to Consulats of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey, Nuevo Laredo pay the extra fee of $26.
